## Understanding

This issue creates the TypeScript CLI foundation for alpha-loop: a Commander.js entry point, YAML config loader, colored logger, and an `init` command. It's the skeleton that all future CLI issues (#74-#78) will build on. The `src/` directory doesn't exist yet, so everything is new files. The bash `loop.sh` must continue working unchanged.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `src/` directory exists with `cli.ts`, `commands/init.ts`, `lib/config.ts`, `lib/logger.ts`
- [ ] `pnpm build` compiles with zero errors (TypeScript strict mode)
- [ ] `npx tsx src/cli.ts --help` shows all commands (`init`, `run`) and options
- [ ] `npx tsx src/cli.ts --version` outputs `0.3.0`
- [ ] `npx tsx src/cli.ts init` creates `.alpha-loop.yaml` with auto-detected repo in a clean directory
- [ ] `npx tsx src/cli.ts init` exits with error and warning when config already exists
- [ ] `loadConfig()` reads `.alpha-loop.yaml` and returns typed `Config` object
- [ ] `loadConfig()` applies env var overrides over config file values
- [ ] `loadConfig()` returns sensible defaults when no config file exists
- [ ] `detectRepo()` correctly parses both HTTPS and SSH GitHub remote URLs
- [ ] Logger outputs colored, timestamped messages matching loop.sh format (`[INFO] HH:MM:SS msg`)
- [ ] `commander` added to `dependencies` in `package.json`
- [ ] `bin` field set to `{"alpha-loop": "./dist/cli.js"}` in `package.json`
- [ ] `build` and `dev` scripts added to `package.json`
- [ ] `tsconfig.json` has `rootDir: "./src"` set
- [ ] `bash scripts/loop.sh --help` still works (loop.sh not modified)
- [ ] All 6 required unit tests pass

## Implementation Plan

### 1. Update `tsconfig.json` (modify)
- Add `"rootDir": "./src"` to `compilerOptions`
- Change `"include"` to `["src/**/*.ts", "tests/**/*.ts"]` to scope compilation

### 2. Update `package.json` (modify)
- Bump version to `"0.3.0"`
- Add `commander: "^13.0.0"` to `dependencies` (yaml already present)
- Add `"bin": { "alpha-loop": "./dist/cli.js" }`
- Add scripts: `"build": "tsc"`, `"dev": "tsx src/cli.ts"`
- Keep existing `loop`, `loop:once`, `loop:dry` scripts unchanged

### 3. Create `src/lib/logger.ts` (new)
- Export a `log` object with methods: `info`, `success`, `warn`, `error`, `step`, `dry`
- Use ANSI escape codes matching loop.sh colors: blue=`\x1b[0;34m`, green=`\x1b[0;32m`, yellow=`\x1b[1;33m`, red=`\x1b[0;31m`, cyan=`\x1b[0;36m`
- Format: `[LABEL]  HH:MM:SS message` (matching loop.sh's `date '+%H:%M:%S'` format)
- No external dependencies

### 4. Create `src/lib/config.ts` (new)
- Define `Config` type with all fields from the issue (repo, repoOwner, project, model, etc.)
- `detectRepo()`: Run `git remote get-url origin`, parse HTTPS (`github.com/owner/repo`) and SSH (`github.com:owner/repo`) patterns via regex, return `"owner/repo"` or `null`
- `loadConfig(overrides?)`: 
  1. Read `.alpha-loop.yaml` if it exists, parse with `yaml` package
  2. Build config with precedence: `overrides` (CLI flags) > env vars > config file > defaults
  3. Auto-detect repo via `detectRepo()` when not otherwise set
  4. Split `repo` into `repoOwner` on `/`
  5. Return fully populated `Config` object
- Defaults match loop.sh: model=`"opus"`, maxTurns=`30`, pollInterval=`60`, baseBranch=`"master"`, labelReady=`"ready"`, etc.
- Use `node:fs`, `node:child_process` (execSync), `node:path`

### 5. Create `src/commands/init.ts` (new)
- Export `initCommand()` async function
- Check if `.alpha-loop.yaml` exists → warn and exit(1)
- Call `detectRepo()` for auto-detection, fall back to `"owner/repo"` placeholder
- Write YAML template matching loop.sh's `run_init()` output format
- Log success with detected repo info

### 6. Create `src/cli.ts` (new)
- Shebang `#!/usr/bin/env node`
- Import Commander, set name/description/version (`0.3.0`)
- Register `init` command → calls `initCommand`
- Register `run` command with all options from issue (`--once`, `--dry-run`, `--model`, `--skip-tests`, `--skip-review`, `--skip-learn`, `--auto-merge`, `--merge-to`) → placeholder action logging "not yet implemented"
- Add stub comments for future subcommands (scan, history, auth, vision)
- Call `program.parse()`

### 7. Run `pnpm install` to install commander

### 8. Verify `pnpm build` succeeds

## Test Plan

Create `tests/lib/config.test.ts`:
- **`loadConfig()` with a config file**: Write a temp `.alpha-loop.yaml`, call `loadConfig()`, assert all fields are populated from file
- **`loadConfig()` with env var overrides**: Set `MODEL=sonnet` env var, call `loadConfig()`, assert env var wins over config file
- **`loadConfig()` with no config file (defaults)**: Call from temp dir with no yaml, assert defaults match (model=opus, maxTurns=30, etc.)
- **`detectRepo()` parses HTTPS URL**: Mock `execSync` to return `https://github.com/owner/repo.git`, assert returns `"owner/repo"`
- **`detectRepo()` parses SSH URL**: Mock `execSync` to return `git@github.com:owner/repo.git`, assert returns `"owner/repo"`

Create `tests/commands/init.test.ts`:
- **init creates config file**: Run in temp dir, assert `.alpha-loop.yaml` created with expected content
- **init fails when config exists**: Create file first, call init, assert it exits/throws with warning

All tests use temp directories (via `node:os` tmpdir + `node:fs` mkdtemp) to avoid polluting the repo. Tests must clean up after themselves.

## What to Test Manually

1. `pnpm build` — should compile with zero errors, output to `dist/`
2. `npx tsx src/cli.ts --help` — should show "alpha-loop" with init and run commands
3. `npx tsx src/cli.ts --version` — should print `0.3.0`
4. `cd /tmp && mkdir test-init && cd test-init && git init && git remote add origin https://github.com/test/repo.git && npx tsx /path/to/src/cli.ts init` — should create `.alpha-loop.yaml` with `repo: test/repo`
5. Run the same init command again — should show warning that config exists and exit 1
6. `bash scripts/loop.sh init` — should still work (bash not modified)
7. `pnpm test` — all tests pass including new ones

## Risks

- **tsconfig `rootDir` change**: Setting `rootDir: "./src"` means `tests/` files won't be included in `tsc` compilation output. The jest config uses `ts-jest` which compiles independently, so tests should still work. But need to verify `include` is set to cover both `src/` and `tests/` for type-checking, or use a separate `tsconfig.build.json` for the `build` script if needed.
- **ESM + ts-jest compatibility**: The jest config currently uses `useESM: false` with ts-jest. Adding ESM imports with `.js` extensions in source code should work because `moduleNameMapper` strips `.js` → resolves to `.ts`. Verify this works with the new files.
- **`execSync` in `detectRepo()`**: If run outside a git repo, `git remote get-url origin` will throw. Must catch this and return `null`. Tests should mock `execSync` rather than depending on the actual git remote.
- **Init command `process.exit(1)`**: Calling `process.exit()` in the init command makes it harder to test. Consider throwing an error or returning an exit code instead, and having the CLI entry point handle the exit.
